      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="overview-box-content">
          <span>What is a credit card?</span>
          <h3>A credit card is a thin rectangular piece of plastic or metal issued by a bank or financial institution that allows you to make purchases on credit.</h3>
          <p>A credit card provides a convenient way to borrow money for purchases, offering benefits such as rewards, fraud protection, and flexible repayment options.</p>

          <ul class="overview-box-list">
            <li><i class="flaticon-check"></i> Convenient payment method accepted worldwide.</li>
            <li><i class="flaticon-check"></i> Allows you to build credit history and improve your credit score.</li>
            <li><i class="flaticon-check"></i> Offers various rewards and cashback programs.</li>
            <li><i class="flaticon-check"></i> Comes with security features like fraud detection and zero liability protection.</li>
